- Data access requests can be compared to the waves generated by these storms;
- The number of users impacted by breaches can be seen as the area affected by each storm.

- 'Garden of users' refers to the user base;
- 'Requests fulfilled' means the requests have been successfully processed;
- 'Visiting the garden' metaphorically refers to making data access requests.

sql:
SELECT 
  (SELECT COUNT(user_id) FROM users) AS total_users,
  (SELECT COUNT(breach_id) FROM breaches) AS total_breaches;

