sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS revoked_reason_count
FROM user_consent
WHERE consent_status = 0 AND consent_revocation_reason IS NOT NULL;

external_knowledge:
- 'explicitly opened the gates of their personal data' refers to users who have explicitly granted consent (`consent_type = 'explicit'` and `consent_status = 1`);
- 'revealing the categories and types of information they've consented to share' refers to the `info_category` and `info_type` columns;
- 'counting the number of sensitive treasures they've unlocked' refers to the count of sensitive data entries (`sensitive_data_count`);
- 'more than one key to their data vault' refers to having more than one user ID in the results (`HAVING COUNT(T1.user_id) > 1`);
